pse and the trachea to shift.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040708,0.058399,0.076821,0.090479,0.10096,0.1063,0.10757,0.10562,0.09811,0.085177,0.070266,0.059583],"unified_progress":[0.039487,0.063759,0.084407,0.095031,0.10048,0.10958,0.10352,0.099424,0.095328,0.085779,0.069748,0.053453]},{"section":11,"text":"The trachea is shifted to the left, which supports the idea of a tension pneumothorax because the pressure from the trapped air would push the trachea to the opposite side.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044442,0.05441,0.072063,0.084884,0.096767,0.10359,0.10629,0.10575,0.1001,0.08815,0.076753,0.0668],"unified_progress":[0.042826,0.06193,0.079464,0.090689,0.097576,0.10497,0.10188,0.099597,0.096523,0.088628,0.074992,0.06092]},{"section":12,"text":"Putting this together, the stabbing in the right intercostal space likely caused a pneumothorax.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03785,0.057407,0.066909,0.075008,0.078054,0.082164,0.086837,0.089195,0.090946,0.098001,0.10623,0.1314],"unified_progress":[0.035266,0.054599,0.065092,0.074899,0.079329,0.085519,0.087046,0.092346,0.096201,0.095687,0.10891,0.1251]},{"section":13,"text":"The subcutaneous emphysema is a sign of the injury, and the absent breath sounds along with tracheal shift point towards a tension pneumothorax.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040498,0.043114,0.056246,0.067286,0.073074,0.079019,0.083792,0.088171,0.091683,0.099042,0.11812,0.15996],"unified_progress":[0.034808,0.045905,0.056385,0.065963,0.072057,0.079223,0.08207,0.089771,0.097884,0.10041,0.12164,0.15388]},{"section":14,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is tension pneumothorax.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022573,0.04309,0.051225,0.058957,0.061854,0.066542,0.073734,0.08144,0.091753,0.1135,0.13938,0.19595],"unified_progress":[0.018737,0.037274,0.047802,0.058014,0.06303